N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 6 ยง 192.1 - Certain cultivars of black currants prohibited

State Regulations

The planting, growing, propagating, cultivating or selling of
plants, roots, or cuttings of cultivated black currants (Ribes nigrum), other
than those cultivars that are immune or resistant to white pine blister rust
disease or currant rust (Cronartium ribicola) as described in section
192.2
of this Part, is prohibited, except in designated fruiting currant districts as defined in section
192.3
of this

Part. Notes
